A vintage 1960s German industrial poster style illustration showing a towering stack of manila folders, rubber stamps, and official documents arranged like a precarious Jenga tower, with a single delicate porcelain teacup balanced perfectly on top, steam rising from it in an elegant spiral. The color palette features muted mustards, deep forest greens, and cream tones with bold geometric shapes in the background suggesting bureaucratic order meeting unexpected elegance. The composition emphasizes the absurd contrast between rigid systematic structure below and the fragile moment of delight above.
